title: Week 9: Scenes from Middle Tennessee
text: Activate your digital access. Week 9: Scenes from Middle Tennessee Riverdale seniors Huston Smith, left, and Noah Flippo, right, cheer for the Riverdale Warriors in the stands during the game against Oakland. Helen Comer / Gannett Tennessee Fullscreen Buy Photo Fans do pushups for every point that Hillsboro made so they did 48 during the the Hunters Lane- Hillsboro game on Friday. John Partipilo / The Tennessean Buy Photo Hillsboro band member Mollie Embody practices on her violin before half time during the Hunter's-Lane Hillsboro game . John Partipilo, John Partipilo / The Tennessean Buy Photo Pope John Paul ll Cheerleaders cheer on their team against Baylor on Friday night. Dave Cardaciotto / For Gannett Tennessee Taeyya Burton and mom Tiffany Caruthers keep warm during the Hunter's Lane-Hillsboro game on Friday. John Partipilo / The Tennessean Fullscreen Senior Oakland football players (L to R) Jacob Frazier (54), Pruitt Jones (15), Cameron Newman (14) and Mark Pruitt hold a jersey of former Oakland football player Jeremy McConville, who died in his sophomore year of high school, as they listen to the national anthem before the start of the Riverdale vs. Oakland game. These seniors were the representatives for the coin toss. Helen Comer / Gannett Tennessee Fullscreen Tricia Patrick wears the number of her son Jeremy McConville as she holds his picture on Senior Night at the Battle of the Boro game on Friday. McConville was an Oakland football player who died in his sophomore year of high school. Jeremy McConville would have been a senior this year and was honored with the other senior football players before the game against Riverdale. Helen Comer / Gannett Tennessee Fullscreen Head referee David Porter asks Riverdale to call a side before the coin toss at the begining of the Riverdale vs. Oakland game,also known as the Battle of the Boro. Oakland players carry the jersey of former teammate Jeremy McConville, who died in his sophomore year. Helen Comer / Gannett Tennessee Fullscreen Buy Photo Kylee Beasley holds her sister Nikyra's flowers on Senior Night at Hillsboro before the team's game against Hunters Lane on Friday night. John Partipilo / The Tennessean Fullscreen Buy Photo Father Ryan High School president Jim McIntyre snaps a selfie with Homecoming queen Jessica Diaz and her escort Cameron Kelley after she was crowned during halftime festivities. George Walker IV / The Tennessean Buy Photo Fullscreen Buy Photo Cameron Kelley presents Jessica Diaz as Father Ryan's 2015 Homecoming queen during their halftime festivities during their game against Brentwood Academy. George Walker IV / The Tennessean Buy Photo Fullscreen Buy Photo Joseph O'Connell escorts Father Ryan cheerleader Sydney Wyatt during their homecoming festivities at halftime of their game against Brentwood Academy on Friday.
